# neo4j-CMS

This is a CLI neo4j CMS tool for [my website](https://aps.web.id/). Its a nice little tool I've been using. To install it you need to create a `secrets/secrets.go` file in the following format:

```
package secrets

var Neo4j_cred = map[string]string{
	"NEO4J_URI":         [neo4j aura URL],
	"NEO4J_USERNAME":    [neo4j db username],
	"NEO4J_PASSWORD":    [neo4j db password],
	"AURA_INSTANCEID":   [neo4j aura instance ID],
	"AURA_INSTANCENAME": [neo4j aura instance name]
}
```

you can get a free instance from the [neo4j Aura site](https://console.neo4j.io/)

# Installation

- Clone this repo.
- Create a `secrets.go` file with the format above in `secrets/` folder.
- Compile using `go build .`


# Usage

You can either run it with `go run . [command]` or use the compiled binary and use the following commands.

Commands:
  - delete-post [post-id] 
  - list-posts
  - edit-post [post-id]
  - write-post

`edit-post` can use partial `post-id`  (first 8 characters is the minimum length), `delete-post` needs the full `post-id` string.

You can write, delete, update, and list new and existing posts in your neo4j database.

# How It Works

This is a very simple app that reads and writes into a [neo4j auradb](https://neo4j.com/product/auradb/) database. It sets up a post by writing:
- created date
- author
- modified date (when edited)
- source (when set to "cms", it is served on the website)
- category* 
- tags*

\* TODO

Interacting with entries uses [Huh](https://github.com/charmbracelet/huh) forms.

# Schemas

## Post
- author
- content
- created date
- modified date
- source
